edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.common

Interface ListInterface<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class of objects to be stored in the list such that T implements the Comparable interface.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedList

    public interface ListInterface<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    An interface for the ADT List. Entries in the list have positions that begin with 0.
    Version:
    4.0, 5.0, 4.1.0
    • initial version based upon Carrano and Henry implementation in the 4th edition of the textbook
    • modified per assignment
    , 5.1.0 2019-08-07
    • revise to match the 5th edition of the textbook
    • revise to match this semester's assignment
    , 5.2.0 2020-07-18
    • remove shuffle() and sort() to EnhancedListInterface, restoring this to the book's functionality
    • update to coding standard
    , 5.3.0 2020-11-08 move sort() and shuffle() back here and make this Iterable to eliminate the second interface
    Author:
    Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, David M Rosenberg

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(T newEntry)
        Adds a new entry to the end of this list. Entries currently in the list are unaffected. The list's size is increased by 1.
        Parameters:
        newEntry - the object to be added as a new entry

      • add

        void add(int newPosition,
         T newEntry)
        Adds a new entry at a specified position within this list. Entries originally at and above the specified position move to the next higher position within the list. The list's size is increased by 1.
        Parameters:
        newPosition - an integer that specifies the desired position of the new entry
        newEntry - the object to be added as a new entry
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if either newPosition < 0 or newPosition >= getLength()

      • clear

        Removes all entries from this list.

      • remove

        T remove(int givenPosition)
        Removes the entry at a given position from this list. Entries originally at positions higher than the given position move to the next lower position within the list, and the list's size is decreased by 1.
        Parameters:
        givenPosition - an integer that indicates the position of the entry to be removed
        Returns:
        a reference to the removed entry
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if either givenPosition < 0 or givenPosition >= getLength() - 1

      • shuffle

        default void shuffle()
        Rearranges the entries in this list in (pseudo-)random order using an algorithm which approximates shuffling a deck of cards.

      • sort

        default void sort()
        Rearranges the entries in this list in non-descending order according to the objects' natural ordering. This sort is stable.
